    coreChallenge: 'The invisible challenge of neurotypicality is assumption blindness — the belief that one\'s own cognitive experience is universal. Neurotypical individuals may struggle with: groupthink and conformity bias, difficulty understanding non-neurotypical perspectives, limited awareness of systemic design bias, and the assumption that effort and willpower are equally available to all brains.',
