    strength: 'Tenacity, depth of analysis, and the ability to see things through. When the Over-Focused brain locks onto a WORTHY target — a social cause, a creative project, a research question — the sustained intensity produces work of extraordinary quality that scattered brains simply cannot match.',
    needToHear: '"Your brain doesn\'t let go easily — and that\'s not always a weakness. The same wiring that makes you replay arguments is what makes you tenacious, thorough, and relentlessly committed to what matters. You need help with the release, not the grip. The grip is your superpower."',
