    prevalence: 'Relatively uncommon but profoundly impactful when present. Frequently misdiagnosed as bipolar disorder due to mood cycling. The "ring" pattern can be associated with brain inflammation, infections (e.g., Lyme disease), allergies, or toxic exposures.',
    mechanism: 'Global cortical hyperactivity — the entire cerebral cortex shows excessive metabolic activity simultaneously. Unlike the localized hypo- or hyper-activity of other types, Ring of Fire represents a brain-wide inflammatory or dysregulatory state. The brain is on fire — not in one region, but everywhere.',
    coreChallenge: 'Extreme, agonizing hypersensitivity to ALL environmental stimuli. Every sense is turned up. Every emotion is amplified. Every thought races. The brain cannot filter, cannot dampen, cannot regulate. It is simultaneously the most overwhelming and the most misunderstood ADD type.',
